\section{Summary Analysis}

\subsection{Aggregate statistics}
Mean coverage across \textbf{45 papers}: \textbf{7.42/10}.
Mean agreement: \textbf{7.93/10}.
27/45 papers scored $\geq 8$ on \emph{both} axes.
8/45 papers scored $\leq 5$ on at least one axis.
Sixteen papers achieved $\geq 9$ on at least one axis.
The honest-negative Godunov-loss entry (4/8) is the sole paper where the
paper's qualitative claim did not reproduce. Correlation(coverage, agreement)
= \textbf{0.70}, consistent with the intended orthogonality of the rubric.

